title: Victorian Labor targets affluent Melbourne suburbs for rezoning to allow 16-storey apartment towers
summary: The state government will take over planning authority for specific areas located near train and tram stops, removing control from local councils. This move aims to streamline development and enhance public transport accessibility. The decision has sparked discussions about local governance and urban planning.

title: Troy review – this fresh Australian take on Homer’s Iliad is a monumental triumph
summary: Tom Wright's production at Malthouse, Melbourne, has received acclaim as one of the theater's best works in years. The performance is described as shocking, chilling, and funny, while also being breathtakingly beautiful. Critics highlight its exceptional quality and emotional impact.
